<p>Guards, through remnants of <strike>isolated</strike> battalions &amp; accidentally isolated Germans, till it had left all our troops behind &amp; nothing lay ahead but enemies.</p>
<p>Soon the advance guard ran into the main German body at a <strike>few</strike> hundred yards or less distance, &amp; planes went up &amp; machine guns constantly rattled out.  In very quick time our boys dug themselves in &amp; by the following night had established a holdable line of defence.</p>
